            <div class="conv-reply">
              <span class="conv-reply-who">[ Resonance.OS ]</span>
              <span class="conv-line">Six rewrites means you were close.</span>
              <span class="conv-line">The intake found the one that had already arrived.</span>
            </div>
          </div>
        </article>
        <article class="conv-card">
          <span class="conv-card-who">[ Lena ] · Teacher, Somatic movement · Copenhagen</span>
          <div class="conv-thread">
            <div class="conv-bubble">"Sent the tagline to my designer the same evening. She said: finally, I can actually build something."</div>
            <div class="conv-reply">
              <span class="conv-reply-who">[ Resonance.OS ]</span>
              <span class="conv-line">That's the handoff this was built for.</span>
            </div>
          </div>
        </article>
        <article class="conv-card">
          <span class="conv-card-who">[ Isabelle ] · Founder, Pilates studio · Paris</span>
          <div class="conv-thread">
            <div class="conv-bubble">"I was expecting something generic. The output had a sentence I wrote at 11pm in question seven, word for word."</div>
            <div class="conv-reply">
              <span class="conv-reply-who">[ Resonance.OS ]</span>
              <span class="conv-line">That's not coincidence.</span>
              <span class="conv-line">That's the whole mechanism.</span>
            </div>
          </div>
        </article>
      </div>
      <!-- duplicate for seamless loop -->
      <div class="conv-set" aria-hidden="true">
        <article class="conv-card">
          <span class="conv-card-who">[ Anna ] · Owner, Pilates studio · Amsterdam</span>
          <div class="conv-thread">
            <div class="conv-bubble">"I sat with the vault for an hour. The tagline is what I'd been trying to write for two years and couldn't."</div>
            <div class="conv-reply"><span class="conv-reply-who">[ Resonance.OS ]</span><span class="conv-line">That's the whole reason this exists.</span><span class="conv-line">You'd already written it. The system just listened.</span></div>
          </div>
        </article>
        <article class="conv-card">
          <span class="conv-card-who">[ Maya ] · Owner, Yoga studio · Berlin</span>
          <div class="conv-thread">
            <div class="conv-bubble">"I've rewritten my bio six times this year. This was the first version I didn't want to immediately change."</div>
            <div class="conv-reply"><span class="conv-reply-who">[ Resonance.OS ]</span><span class="conv-line">Six rewrites means you were close.</span><span class="conv-line">The intake found the one that had already arrived.</span></div>
          </div>
        </article>
        <article class="conv-card">
          <span class="conv-card-who">[ Lena ] · Teacher, Somatic movement · Copenhagen</span>
          <div class="conv-thread">
            <div class="conv-bubble">"Sent the tagline to my designer the same evening. She said: finally, I can actually build something."</div>
            <div class="conv-reply"><span class="conv-reply-who">[ Resonance.OS ]</span><span class="conv-line">That's the handoff this was built for.</span></div>
          </div>
        </article>
        <article class="conv-card">
          <span class="conv-card-who">[ Isabelle ] · Founder, Pilates studio · Paris</span>
          <div class="conv-thread">
            <div class="conv-bubble">"I was expecting something generic. The output had a sentence I wrote at 11pm in question seven, word for word."</div>
            <div class="conv-reply"><span class="conv-reply-who">[ Resonance.OS ]</span><span class="conv-line">That's not coincidence.</span><span class="conv-line">That's the whole mechanism.</span></div>
          </div>
        </article>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

</div><!-- /.panel-stack -->

</Base>

<style>
  /* Two-product overview cards (home only) */
  .prod-cards {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr;
    gap: clamp(1rem, 2vw, 1.5rem);
    margin-top: 2.5rem;
  }
  .prod-card {
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    background: var(--bg);
    border: 1px solid var(--rule);
    border-radius: var(--rad);
    padding: clamp(1.75rem, 3vw, 2.5rem);
    transition: border-color var(--color-ease, 0.4s ease-out);
  }
  .prod-card:hover { border-color: rgba(247, 91, 29, 0.35); }
  .prod-card-lbl {
    font-family: var(--fm); font-size: 0.6rem; text-transform: uppercase;
    letter-spacing: 0.1em; color: var(--accent); margin-bottom: 1.25rem;
  }
  .prod-card-ttl {
    font-family: var(--fu); font-size: clamp(1.35rem, 2.2vw, 1.85rem);
    font-weight: 700; letter-spacing: -0.03em; line-height: 1.05;
    color: var(--ink); margin-bottom: 0.875rem;
  }
  .prod-card-desc {
    font-family: var(--fu); font-size: 0.9375rem; line-height: 1.6;
    color: var(--ink-m); margin-bottom: 1.5rem; max-width: 40ch;
  }
  .prod-card-meta {
    font-family: var(--fm); font-size: 0.6rem; text-transform: uppercase;
    letter-spacing: 0.08em; color: var(--ink-m); margin-bottom: 1.5rem;
  }
  .prod-card-go {
    margin-top: auto;
    font-family: var(--fu); font-size: 0.9375rem; font-weight: 600;
    color: var(--ink); letter-spacing: -0.01em;
    transition: color var(--color-ease, 0.4s ease-out);
  }
  .prod-card-go span { display: inline-block; transition: transform var(--fast-ease, 0.5s cubic-bezier(.84,0,.16,1)); }
  .prod-card:hover .prod-card-go { color: var(--accent); }
  .prod-card:hover .prod-card-go span { transform: translateX(4px); }

  @media (max-width: 760px) {
    .prod-cards { grid-template-columns: 1fr; }
  }
</style>

<script>
  // Testimonials: pause scrolling when a card is hovered (desktop)
  // or tapped (mobile). Tap again to resume. Replaces the previous
  // wrap-level :hover pause so the strip only stops when the user is
  // actually reading a card.
  (function(){
    const track = document.querySelector('#testimonials .conv-track');
    const cards = document.querySelectorAll('#testimonials .conv-card');
    if (!track || !cards.length) return;
    const isCoarse = window.matchMedia('(pointer: coarse)').matches;
    if (isCoarse) {
      cards.forEach(c => c.addEventListener('click', e => {
        e.preventDefault();
        track.classList.toggle('is-paused');
      }));
    } else {
      cards.forEach(c => {
        c.addEventListener('mouseenter', () => track.classList.add('is-paused'));
        c.addEventListener('mouseleave', () => track.classList.remove('is-paused'));
      });
    }
  })();
</script>
